# CSS

Css stands for **Cascading Style Sheets**

## Code tips
* D.R.Y
  * Don't 
  * Repeat
  * Yourself 

Avoid inline styles
Avoid if can Head of html styles
Always try and tdo external CSS

## CSS
Css allows you to create rules that control the way individual boxes and thier content are displayed on a web page. 

CSS assocaites style with html elements

*Selector* **P** *declaration* {} 
insde *declaration* {
**property: **Value**

CSS properties affect how elements are displayed. 

The <link> element tells html where to find the css rules

href specifies a path to the css file
The type should always be type="text/css"

*example* <link href ="css/styles.css" type="text/css"

* Css selectors on page 238 of text. 

## Color 
*Rgb values
* hex codes
* color names

It is important to have enough contrast so that the text is legible

Can set opacity
* opacity: 0.5;
*sets opacity to 50%*

